a/boone/"], "contributor": ["university of north carolina at chapel hill library, chapel hill, nc"], "date": "1930-11-13", "dates": ["1930-11-13"], "description": ["EIGHT LOCAL AFFAIRS Dr and Mrs Fred Hodges are moving this week into an apartment in the Cook home on Main Street Miss Louise Critcher spent last weekend with Mr and Mrs Clyde Ritch in Greensboro N C Dr and Mrs J M Gaither are spending the week in Atlanta where the doctor is transacting business Mrs James Moore will entertain the Maids and Matrons Club on Sati urday night November 15th at 745 n m Mr and Mrs Ernest Comer of Greensboro were guests of Dr and Mrs G K Moose during the first of this week Ml Wilej H Swift prominent Greensboro attorney is spending a few days visiting with home folks in this county There will be a meeting of the lo cal ParentTeacher Association a the Demonstration School building Thursday afternoon at oclock A full attendance is urged Citizens of North Carolina open your hearts and loosen your purse strings to the Orphan Homes of the State at Thanksgiving this year to a greater degree than you have ever done before The need is urgent Mr G C Greer and family of Zionville left Saturday for Patton Calif where they will spend the win ter with"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-12T17:31:08.455Z", "group": ["ndnp/ncu", "university-of-north-carolina-chapel-hill-library-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82007642/1930-11-13/ed-1/?sp=8", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_appling_ver02:data:sn82007642:00279558194:1930111301:0792/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=420&w=287", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_appling_ver02:data:sn82007642:00279558194:1930111301:0792/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=841&w=575", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_appling_ver02/data/sn82007642/00279558194/1930111301/0792.xm